---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import FAQ from '../components/FAQ.astro';
import bottlingLine from '../assets/images/bottling-line.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="CappingChucks.com | Precision Capping Chucks and Headsets"
    description="Technical reference for precision capping chucks, capping headsets, and rotary capper tooling. Chuck classifications, compatibility factors, and troubleshooting for packaging engineers."
    ogTitle="CappingChucks.com | Capping Chucks and Headsets"
    ogDescription="Technical reference for precision capping chucks and headsets. Chuck classifications, compatibility factors, and troubleshooting for rotary and inline capping systems."
>
    <header class="pt-20 border-b border-border">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-16">
            <h1 class="mb-4">Precision Capping Chucks & Headsets</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-light leading-relaxed max-w-xl">A capping chuck is the tooling component on a capping machine spindle that grips a closure and applies controlled torque to thread it onto a bottle. This is the technical reference: chuck classifications, OEM cross-references, and calibration data for rotary and inline capping lines.</p>
        </div>
        <figure class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
            <Picture
                src={bottlingLine}
                alt="Wine bottles moving through a rotary capping station on an industrial bottling line"
                class="w-full h-64 object-cover object-center sm:h-80 rounded-lg"
                widths={[600, 900, 1200]}
                sizes="100vw"
                formats={['avif', 'webp']}
                quality={80}
                loading="eager"
            />
            <figcaption class="mt-2 px-6 font-mono text-[0.68rem] text-ink-faint">Rotary capping station on a high-speed bottling line. Photo: Pexels</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section id="overview" class="py-16 border-b border-border">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-6">Technical Overview</h2>

                <div class="space-y-4 text-[0.95rem] text-ink-light">
                    <p>A capping chuck is the torque-transmitting interface between a capping turret spindle and the closure. It sits at the bottom of each spindle station on a rotary capper, or on the descending head of an inline unit. The chuck grips the closure's outer shell, applies controlled rotational torque, and threads the cap onto the container finish to a target removal-torque spec.</p>

                    <p>Torque consistency depends on the chuck's internal drive mechanism (magnetic hysteresis, friction clutch, pneumatic cylinder, or servo). A properly calibrated chuck should deliver full thread engagement, preserve tamper-evident features during application, and apply enough seal compression to meet the package's leak and retention requirements.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="spec-panel mt-8">
                    <h3 class="mb-3 text-sm">Key Performance Parameters</h3>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Application Torque Range</span><span class="spec-value">Varies by closure and headset design</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Torque CV% Target</span><span class="spec-value">Set by package spec and process capability goals</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Line Speed Capability</span><span class="spec-value">Depends on machine platform and closure format</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Closure Dia. Range</span><span class="spec-value">Determined by chuck geometry and machine envelope</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Service Life</span><span class="spec-value">Depends on materials, maintenance, and duty cycle</span></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="py-16 border-b border-border">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-6">Reference Guides</h2>

                <div class="space-y-8">
                    <a href="/chuck-types/" class="hub-link">
                        <h3>Capping Chuck Types</h3>
                        <p>Magnetic hysteresis, friction, pneumatic, and vacuum chucks. How each type works, when to use it, and which closure formats they handle.</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="/capping-headsets/" class="hub-link">
                        <h3>Capping Headsets</h3>
                        <p>Magnetic, spring-clutch, and hysteresis headset assemblies. Torque delivery mechanisms, ROPP tooling, and headset selection by line speed.</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="/oem-compatibility/" class="hub-link">
                        <h3>OEM Compatibility Index</h3>
                        <p>Reference index for common Zalkin, Krones, AROL, CSI, and Tedelta capping platforms and the fit-up factors that affect aftermarket replacement work.</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="/troubleshooting/" class="hub-link">
                        <h3>Troubleshooting & Calibration</h3>
                        <p>Diagnostic procedures for cap scuffing, torque scatter, stripped TE bands, cross-threading, vacuum loss, and undertorque conditions.</p>
                    </a>

                    <a href="/glossary/" class="hub-link">
                        <h3>Glossary</h3>
                        <p>Definitions for knurling, thread pitch, top load, slip torque, bridge count, closure ovalization, and other capping terminology.</p>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <FAQ />
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
